  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/97163aef-e2e4-4203-9c8e-fd739cdaa8e9/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "f9163204fc9527c8",
    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nAs the Senior Tax Manager, you will be a strategic advisor within Snowflake’s finance organization. You will be responsible for the U.S. corporate income tax provision and compliance function. This is an amazing opportunity to join a groundbreaking organization and make an immediate impact.\n\nThis is a hybrid role that can be based in either Menlo Park, CA or Dublin, CA.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n - Prepare and review quarterly and year-end global corporate income tax provision in accordance with ASC 740, including ASC 740-10 reserve calculation, ASC 718 stock based compensation and ASC 805 acquisition accounting\n\n - Prepare and review financial statement disclosures related to taxes\n\n - Prepare and review U.S. income tax compliance and reporting including U.S. federal and state income tax returns\n\n - Prepare multi-year forecast tax provision, including Pillar 2 and CAMT effects, to support financial planning and analysis and budgeting\n\n - Write and review technical memos to internal and external parties to address tax issues raised in various business transactions\n\n - Assist with tax accounting processes, perform and document S-OX controls for accounting and reporting\n\n - Manage ongoing efforts to automate and optimize the tax compliance and quarterly tax provision processes\n\n - Monitor changes in US accounting standards and U.S. and foreign tax laws to ensure income tax impact is properly considered\n\n - Develop a trusted network of business partners in other functions including Accounting, Treasury, Legal, FP\u0026A, and Human Resources\n\n - Train and develop junior staff members\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS:\n\n - BA/BS Degree in Accounting, Tax and/or Finance/ CPA\n\n - Experience with Big 4 firm and in-house tax department with a minimum of 7 years supervisory experience\n\n - Minimum of 13 years in depth experience with corporate income tax compliance and ASC 740 accounting including hands on experience calculating quarterly tax provision for large multinational public companies\n\n - Proven ability to adapt to a complex, fast paced, rapidly evolving, and highly demanding work environment\n\n - Demonstrated ability to develop a strong network of internal and external business partners\n\n - Must be a self-starter who handles multiple projects, managing competing priorities with minimal supervision\n\n - Positive attitude, eager to learn and willing to take on challenges\n\n - Knowledge of Workday ERP a plus\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
